&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Staff Nurse - School Nursing - Reading &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;(Band 5)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you regard yourself as an enthusiastic and dynamic qualified Band 5 Staff Nurse then you may be suitable to join our forward thinking, vibrant School Nursing team in Reading. Whether you are an experienced Staff Nurse or have recently qualified, we will ensure you receive devoted, effective support from both your manager and colleagues within your team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work within the Reading area to deliver core and targeted services to children aged 5-19 and their families. You will require excellent interpersonal skills, the ability to work in partnership with other teams and agencies, along with great communication skills and a passion for working with children and families.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A commitment to team working, flexibility and working with partners is essential, as you will collaborate with schools, children’s social care and other Public Health partners to deliver the universal Healthy Child Programme&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Some of the general responsibilities include; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To work with the School Nurse to deliver targeted support to children, young people, and their families, where there is an identified health need, such as the coordination of health care plans&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To undertake training of school staff in the administration of emergency treatment and care (e.g. Severe Allergic Reaction, Asthma and Epilepsy) and provides updates as required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To assist in the delivery of nurse led clinics, i.e. enuresis and referral clinics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To work independently within educational settings, in the planning, implementation and evaluation of health promotion activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Where the role will be based:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If successful your base will be Southcote Clinic in Reading however your role will require you to visit schools and homes across Reading and surrounding areas (mileage will be compensated).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Work base – &lt;/strong&gt;Southcote Clinic, Reading&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Some of the benefits of joining our team/trust:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We have been awarded an overall rating of ‘Good’ with the CQC&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We have been awarded a rating of ‘Outstanding’ in the Well Led domain&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Flexible working&lt;/strong&gt; opportunities and a strong emphasis on &lt;strong&gt;work life balance&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent &lt;strong&gt;learning and development opportunities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Salary sacrifice scheme for a new car.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lease car&lt;/strong&gt; scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generous maternity, paternity and adoption leave for eligible staff&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced IT enablement and support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Confidential telephone care service providing independent staff support and advice.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The 3 “requirements” in order for you to be considered for this role;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You must be a &lt;strong&gt;Registered Nurse &lt;/strong&gt;active on the&lt;strong&gt; NMC register&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to &lt;strong&gt;carry/manoeuvre &lt;/strong&gt;light to moderate loads&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will hold a valid &lt;strong&gt;UK drivers license&lt;/strong&gt; with &lt;strong&gt;access to a vehicle&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Should you match up to the 3 specs listed above, and if you are looking to work somewhere that is unconditionally respectful to young people and their families, that values their staff as individuals and continuously strives to be the best service it can be then we would recommend you make your application to work here at Berkshire Healthcare NHS Foundation Trust!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details about this role or questions in general about working for Berkshire Healthcare please contact Karen Jacobs&lt;strong&gt; on 07823 551367 or via email &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;karen.jacobs@berkshire.nhs.uk&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
